post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_22471925_22472200_0": {"length": 12, "quality": 0.8571428571428571, "section_id": 3338}}, "n3337": {"so_22471925_22472200_0": {"length": 13, "quality": 0.9285714285714286, "section_id": 3208}}, "n4659": {"so_22471925_22472200_0": {"length": 11, "quality": 0.7857142857142857, "section_id": 4105}}}, "22472200": {"Id": "22472200", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>When you throw, an exception object is constructed that has the same type as the operand of <code>throw</code> with top-level cv-qualifiers removed (if you throw an array or function, they also decay to their corresponding pointers).</p>\n<p>So what you did is a no-go, I'm afraid.</p>\n<p>C++ standard chapter [except.throw] \u00a75:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_22471925_22472200_0\">When the thrown object is a class object, the copy/move constructor and the destructor shall be accessible, even if the copy/move operation is elided (12.8).</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "947836", "LastActivityDate": "2014-03-18T07:14:56.030", "Score": "5", "CreationDate": "2014-03-18T06:49:58.020", "ParentId": "22471925", "CommentCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "947836", "LastEditDate": "2014-03-18T07:14:56.030"}, "22471925": {"ViewCount": "88", "Body": "<p>I have a class <code>CustomException</code>, that implements <code>std::exception</code>, in which I explicitely deleted the copy and move constructors. When I throw an exception of that class, there are compiling errors for calling the deleted constructors.</p>\n<p>Are CustomException instances being created somewhere? What objects are created when the exception is thrown?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "22472200", "Title": "Are std::exception objects created when an exception is thrown?", "CreationDate": "2014-03-18T06:32:30.273", "Id": "22471925", "CommentCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2014-03-18T07:14:56.030", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "1813345", "Tags": "<c++><exception><c++11><copy-constructor><move-constructor>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});